What is a server ?

A server is a computer that listens on a network port at all times, waiting for requests.
When it receives one, it processes it and sends back a response.

What is the role of the domain name ?

The domain name is a human-readable address.
Instead of memorizing the IP address 8.8.8.8, the user just types www.foobar.com.
The DNS then translates that name into the IP address to reach the server.

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com ?

A record: it maps a domain name to an IPv4 address.

What is the role of the web server ?

It receives HTTP requests, serves static files directly, and forwards dynamic requests to the application server.

What is the role of the application server ?

The application server executes your code, contains the business logic, queries MySQL and generates the HTML response.

What is the role of the database ?

MySQL receives SQL queries from the application server and returns raw data and it never communicates directly with the browser.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website ?

HTTP is the communication protocol between the browser and the server.

SPOF :
This is a Single Point of Failure.
If the server goes down, the entire website is unavailable. There is no redundancy.

Downtime :
To deploy new code, Nginx needs to be restarted.
During that restart, the website is unavailable to users.

No scalability :
A single server has limited resources.
It cannot handle sudden traffic spikes.
There is no way to add capacity without replacing the entire machine.

